## Scenario 1 — Chemical Spill at Loading Dock During Offloading
##
## Three-agency compound activation (DOT + EPA + OSHA). Transport
## context at the dock: spill is "incidental to movement" per
## 49 CFR 171.1(c)(2)-(3). Spill reaches ground outside containment,
## uncontrolled, above RQ.
##
## This ASK must stay true across every ontology revision. Baseline
## triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1178).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_ChemSpill_LoadingDock rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:ChemicalHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:TransportAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:LoadingDock ,
                                  ehs:FullRelease ,
                                  ehs:AboveReportableQuantity ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:DOT_Framework ,
                                  ehs:EPA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:OSHA_Framework .
}
